The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem related to permutations, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of approximation algorithms and the analysis of their performance also points towards the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The study of the Symmetric Group and the algebraic formalism used in the proposed algorithm could fit into the Group Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the use of numerical methods to obtain upper bounds for the transposition distance could also relate to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category.
